features: ORGANIC COTTON: Our Highly Absorbent Organic Tampons are made of 100% organic cotton only. Natural tampons with ultra-absorbent cores and cover to prevent fibers and nasty filaments from falling apart inside your body. They’re safe, non toxic tampons and chemical-free.
WIDTH EXPANSION - No leaks as our organic tampons expand width-wise to fit all bodies.

COMFORTABLE AND EASY: Because of their soft round end-tip, our individual tampons are comfortable and easy to insert. Simply take your tampon, twist the top in the opposite direction of the bottom, and push!

GENTLE ON SKIN: Our super, regular and super-plus tampons are specially made for sensitive skin. Vegan, dye-free, and fragrance-free, these tampons are gentle yet effective heavy periods solutions designed with every woman in mind

EARTH-FRIENDLY & SUSTAINABLE: Compared to other tampons on the market, our tampons are better for the environment. Apart from being made completely of organic cotton, each tampon is wrapped in recycled paper and packed in a tube

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I am sensitive to certain tampons. Some will cause discomfort, burning , itching for some reason as I’ve gotten older. These are similar to cvs organic cardboard applicators, that are out of stock now due to inflation 🤨. They work for me. So purity most be legit with these tampons, plus they come in cool cylinder cardboard box

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I really, really wanted to love these. Great concept, I can get behind organic and sustainable. However, the product needs to function and that's where these fell short. The applicator wasn't an issue for me, but they should provide more obvious instructions that you have to twist the applicator before pushing (I'd guess most of the negative reviews about the applicator didn't realize thus). My biggest complaint is that they are designed to absorb lengthwise only, not widthwise. Thus, you're either dealing with constant leaks or your blowing through super tampons at an alarming clip. I can't justify the price for the number I was going through and the hassle of still experiencing leaks. If they changed the design of how they absorb, I'd try them again. For now, I'm out.
